No more flying after 9pm according to Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - No more flying after 9pm. That's the word from Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula. He has updated the country on transport regulations under the Level 3 lockdown. WATCH: Lockdown Level 3 explained Mbalula said the curfew has a direct impact on airline schedules. "As a consequence, the South African Civil Aviation Authority has already issued to consider the curfew in revising their schedules...meaning there will no longer be a last flight like 9pm. "It means by 9pm all fights scheduled would've been completed for the next duration of this curfew."